id: pmc-874d
title: Classifier misroutes Issues with CLI command-name titles (update/change) to Changed not Fixed
description: "The keyword classifier scans [type, tags, title] and matches the Changed needle 'update'/'updated' against CLI command names like 'pm update' in Issue titles. pm-cli's Issue 'pm update doesn't accept --expected/--actual aliases that pm close accepts' was filed under Changed solely because its title contains the command word 'update'. Same class of defect as #19 (CLI flag tokens leaking into Added). Fix: let a bug-like item TYPE (issue/bug/bugfix/defect) win over the weak Changed keywords (update/change/refactor/improve), keeping explicit security/removed/fix/feature signals ahead; non-bug types (task/chore) still route 'update dependency ...' to Changed."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[2]: bug,classifier
created_at: "2026-05-29T00:25:48.699Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-29T00:26:00.823Z"
deadline: "2026-05-30T00:00:00.000Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 30
acceptance_criteria: "Issue/Bug/Defect titled with command words update/change route to Fixed; chore 'update dependency' stays Changed; explicit feature tag still wins; regression tests added; dist rebuilt; changelog:check passes"
reviewer: steve
severity: medium
resolution: "Reordered classifyItem: bug-like item type (issue/bug/bugfix/defect) now defaults to Fixed BEFORE the weak change/update/refactor/improve keyword bucket, while explicit security/removed/fix/feature signals stay ahead. Added regression tests for command-name keywords in Issue titles and for non-bug 'update dependency' chores staying Changed."
expected_result: Issues titled after CLI commands (pm update ...) classify as Fixed; chores 'update dependency' stay Changed; explicit feature tag still wins
actual_result: All 42 tests pass; typecheck + dist rebuilt
fixed_version: 2026.5.29-1
